「'''人民公敵'''」（{{lang-en|Enemies of the People}}）是英國報章《[[每日郵報|每日郵報]]》2016年11月4日首頁的[[新聞標題|新聞標題]]，由政治編輯{{tsl|en|James Slack|詹士·史勒}}所撰寫<ref name="Phipps">{{cite news|last=Phipps|first=Claire|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/nov/04/enemies-of-the-people-british-newspapers-react-judges-brexit-ruling|title=British newspapers react to judges' Brexit ruling: 'Enemies of the people'|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2016-11-04|accessdate=2017-02-03|archive-date=2019-05-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190525120311/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/nov/04/enemies-of-the-people-british-newspapers-react-judges-brexit-ruling|dead-url=no}}</ref>，報導法院頒下有關[[英国宪法|英国宪法]]是否容許[[英國政府|英國政府]]動用[[皇家特權|皇家特權]]啟動[[英國脫歐|脫歐]]程序的裁決，最終三名英國法官裁定政府需事先取得[[英国议会|國會]]的[[國會法令|法令]]同意。輿論廣泛批評新聞頭條不恰當地譴責司法機關，強調司法獨立於行政機關。 

== 背景 ==
[[英國去留歐盟公投|2016年6月的公投]]決定英國脫離歐盟，政府考慮動用[[皇家特權|皇家特權]]去引用《[[里斯本条约|歐盟條約]]》第50條作出通知，即啟動[[英國脫歐|脫歐]]程序<ref name="Phipps" />。不過[[英格蘭及威爾斯高等法院|英格蘭及威爾斯高等法院]]在{{tsl|en|R (Miller) v Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union|女皇（米勒）訴脫離歐盟事務大臣|米勒案}}裁定政府需要取得國會的同意，才可以啟動脫歐程序，隨即觸發脫歐派部分人士不滿<ref name="independent" />。

「人民公敵」一題由{{tsl|en|James Slack|詹士·史勒}}撰寫，並獲得{{tsl|en|Paul Dacre|保羅·達卡}}批准出版<ref>{{cite journal|work={{tsl|en|The Oldie||The Oldie}}|date=March 2017|p=34|title=Moralist, monarchist and Brexiteer-in-chief|first=Stephen|last=Fay}}</ref>。《每日郵報》批評法院特意阻撓[[英國脫歐|英國脫歐]]進程，並在報章刊出高等法院三名法官的照片：[[英格蘭及威爾斯首席法官|首席法官]]{{tsl|en|John Thomas (judge)|約翰·湯瑪士|湯瑪士勳爵}}、[[主事官|主事官]]{{tsl|en|Terence Etherton|特倫斯·魏華頓}}爵士、法官{{tsl|en|Philip Sales|菲臘·世斯|世斯勳爵}}<ref name=independent>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/media/daily-mail-nazi-propaganda-front-page-ipso-complaints-brexit-eu-enemies-of-the-people-a7409836.html|title=Daily Mail's 'Enemies of the People' front page receives more than 1,000 complaints to IPSO|newspaper=The Independent|date=2016-11-10|accessdate=2017-02-03|archive-date=2020-04-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401235709/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/media/daily-mail-nazi-propaganda-front-page-ipso-complaints-brexit-eu-enemies-of-the-people-a7409836.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/27/opinion/sunday/is-donald-trump-mr-brexit.html|title=Is Donald Trump ‘Mr. Brexit’?|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2017-01-27|accessdate=2017-02-03|archive-date=2021-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120214849/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/27/opinion/sunday/is-donald-trump-mr-brexit.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。《{{tsl|en|MailOnline|網上郵報}}》起初更形容魏華頓是「公開出櫃前奧運劍術運動員」<ref name="Duffy">{{cite web|url=http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2016/11/03/the-daily-mail-is-very-upset-because-an-openly-gay-judge-ruled-on-brexit/|title=The Daily Mail is very upset because an 'openly gay judge' ruled on Brexit|last=Duffy|first=Nick|work={{tsl|en|PinkNews||PinkNews}}|date=2016-11-03|accessdate=2017-02-09|archive-date=2016-11-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161106152102/http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2016/11/03/the-daily-mail-is-very-upset-because-an-openly-gay-judge-ruled-on-brexit/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，直至在社交媒體引起爭議後才刪改<ref name="Nelson">{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/mailonline-online-attacks-brexit-judge-for-being-openly-gay_uk_581b344ee4b0ab6e4c1ba5ff|title=MailOnline Attacks Brexit Judge For Being 'Openly Gay'|last=Nelson|first=Sara C|work=[[赫芬顿邮报|Huffington Post]]|date=2016-11-03|accessdate=2017-02-09|archive-date=2018-09-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180910014658/https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/mailonline-online-attacks-brexit-judge-for-being-openly-gay_uk_581b344ee4b0ab6e4c1ba5ff|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Blair">{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/jk-rowling-brexit-legal-challenge-twitter-response-daily-mail-headline-openly-gay-fencer-judge-a7396941.html|title=J. K. Rowling responds perfectly to Mail Online headline referencing judges's sexuality after Brexit High Court ruling|last=Blair|first=Olivia|date=2016-11-04|work=[[獨立報|The Independent]]|accessdate=2017-02-09|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108110817/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/jk-rowling-brexit-legal-challenge-twitter-response-daily-mail-headline-openly-gay-fencer-judge-a7396941.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。前首席法官{{tsl|en|Igor Judge, Baron Judge|義葛·澤曙}}批評報章的攻擊令人「非常不安」，尤其是疑似恐同的評論<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2016/11/08/former-lord-chief-justice-attacks-homophobic-campaign-against-brexit-judge/|title=Former Lord Chief Justice Attacks Homophobic Campaign Against Brexit|work=Pink News|date=2016-11-08|accessdate=2017-02-14|archive-date=2020-12-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201205093645/https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2016/11/08/former-lord-chief-justice-attacks-homophobic-campaign-against-brexit-judge/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==餘波==
{{tsl|en|Independent Press Standards Organisation|獨立傳媒標準組織}}收到超過1,000項有關本報道的投訴，斥責報社的報導失實、涉嫌恐嚇和歧視，違反行為準則<ref name=independent/><ref>{{cite journal|work=Discourse, Context & Media|date=April 2018|title="Enemies of the people": Populist performances in the Daily Mail reporting of the Article 50 case|first=Ruth|last=Breeze|doi=10.1016/j.dcm.2018.03.008}}</ref>。《[[商业内幕|商业内幕]]》強烈抨擊報導扭曲事實，質疑可被視為意圖破壞法官形象和危害他們的安全<ref>{{cite news|url=http://uk.businessinsider.com/brexit-high-court-article-50-judges-mail-express-front-page-2016-11|title=People are furious at the ''Daily Mail'' front page branding the Article 50 judges ‘Enemies of the People'|work=Business Insider|date=2016-11-04|accessdate=2017-02-03|archive-date=2018-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180603115858/http://uk.businessinsider.com/brexit-high-court-article-50-judges-mail-express-front-page-2016-11|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2016年11月，{{tsl|en|Anglican Bishop of Leeds|列斯主教}}{{tsl|en|Nick Baines (bishop)|力克·炳斯}}認為公眾應「非常警覺」《每日郵報》的報導<ref name=independent/>。[[廖柏嘉|廖柏嘉勳爵]]在2017年2月接受BBC訪問時提及本報導，形容是挑戰法律底線<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-38986228|title=Attacks on judges undermine law – Supreme Court president|work=BBC News|date=2017-02-16|accessdate=2017-02-16|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111175201/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-38986228|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[司法大臣_(英國)|司法大臣]][[伊丽莎白·特拉斯|伊丽莎白·特拉斯]]透過聲明回應包括《每日郵報》、《[[每日快報|每日快報]]》和《[[太陽報_(英國)|太陽報]]》等報章對高等法院判決的批評，強調要捍衛司法獨立和司法公正<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/law/2016/nov/05/barristers-urge-liz-truss-to-condemn-attacks-on-brexit-ruling-judges|title=Liz Truss defends judiciary after Brexit ruling criticism|work=The Guardian|date=2016-11-05|accessdate=2017-02-11|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108095740/https://www.theguardian.com/law/2016/nov/05/barristers-urge-liz-truss-to-condemn-attacks-on-brexit-ruling-judges|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/bar-council-liz-truss-brexit-ruling-decision-serious-unjustified-attacks-judiciary-judges-high-court-a7399356.html|title=Liz Truss breaks her silence but fails to condemn backlash over Brexit ruling|work=The Independent|accessdate=2017-02-11|last=Worley|first=Will|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108140533/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/bar-council-liz-truss-brexit-ruling-decision-serious-unjustified-attacks-judiciary-judges-high-court-a7399356.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。曾促使政府表態的[[英格蘭及威爾斯大律師公會|大律師公會]]主席表示，伊丽莎白·特拉斯應該清楚地表明維護司法機構，以及譴責報章的攻擊性言論<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-37883576|title=Brexit ruling: Lord Chancellor backs judiciary amid row|work=BBC News|date=2016-11-05|accessdate=2017-02-03|archive-date=2016-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105122354/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-37883576|dead-url=no}}</ref>。政府聲明只有三句，被批過於輕描淡寫聲明。前政府大臣[[安娜·苏布里|安娜·苏布里]]表示卓慧思「有職責譴責針對司法機關的恐同攻擊和誹謗」<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/nov/05/lawyers-war-liz-truss-over-abuse-judges-brexit-barristers|title=Brexit: lawyers confront Liz Truss over ‘dangerous’ abuse of judges|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2016-11-05|accessdate=2017-02-03|archive-date=2020-11-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130212834/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/nov/05/lawyers-war-liz-truss-over-abuse-judges-brexit-barristers|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

政府其後提出上訴，但在2017年1月被[[英国最高法院|最高法院]]駁回，廖柏嘉勳爵指出「政府需要有國會法令才可動用第50條」<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-38720320|title=Brexit: Supreme Court says Parliament must give Article 50 go-ahead|work=BBC News|date=2017-01-24|accessdate=2017-02-03|archive-date=2020-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229215946/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-38720320|dead-url=no}}</ref>。大律師公會亦發起宣傳活動，教導中學生英國司法獨立和公正的重要性<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/education/2017/01/24/barristers-launch-pr-drive-schools-explain-judges-not-enemies/|title=Barristers launch PR drive in schools to explain why judges are not the 'enemies of the people'|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=2017-01-24|accessdate=2017-02-03|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112020114/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/education/2017/01/24/barristers-launch-pr-drive-schools-explain-judges-not-enemies/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2017年2月10日，詹士·史勒獲任命為時任首相[[文翠珊|文翠珊]]的官方發言人<ref>{{cite news|last=McTague|first=Tom|url=http://www.politico.eu/article/theresa-may-gets-her-alastair-campbell/|title=Theresa May gets her Alastair Campbell|work=Politico|date=2017-01-31|accessdate=2017-01-31|archive-date=2020-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129054350/https://www.politico.eu/article/theresa-may-gets-her-alastair-campbell/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Asthana|first=Anushka|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2017/jan/31/journalist-james-slack-daily-mail-theresa-may-spokesman-no-10|title=Journalist James Slack tipped to become Theresa May's spokesman|work=The Guardian|date=2017-01-31|accessdate=2017-01-31|archive-date=2020-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128172314/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2017/jan/31/journalist-james-slack-daily-mail-theresa-may-spokesman-no-10|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/prime-ministers-official-spokesperson-appointed-james-slack|title=James Slack will be the new Prime Minister's Official Spokesperson|publisher=H,M. Government|date=2017-02-10|accessdate=2017-02-10|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112000652/https://www.gov.uk/government/news/prime-ministers-official-spokesperson-appointed-james-slack|dead-url=no}}</ref>。同年3月1日，卓慧思在上議院憲法委員會表示「我認為由一名政府大臣去判斷這個頭條可否接受是危險的，因為我十分相信司法獨立、也同時非常相信新聞自由」<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.pressgazette.co.uk/enemies-of-the-people-lord-chancellor-liz-truss-says-it-would-be-dangerous-to-tell-daily-mail-want-to-print|title=Liz Truss defends press after Brexit ruling criticism|work=The Press Gazette|date=2017-03-01|accessdate=2020-04-05|archive-date=2020-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126220319/https://www.pressgazette.co.uk/enemies-of-the-people-lord-chancellor-liz-truss-says-it-would-be-dangerous-to-tell-daily-mail-want-to-print|dead-url=no}}</ref>，隨即遭受湯瑪士勳爵的譴責，認為傳媒不可被指摘的說法「完全極其錯誤」<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/mar/22/lord-chief-justice-castigates-liz-truss-for-failing-to-defend-judges|title=Lord chief justice attacks Liz Truss for failing to back article 50 judges|first=Owen|last=Bowcott|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2017-03-22|accessdate=2017-04-27|archive-date=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130141358/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/mar/22/lord-chief-justice-castigates-liz-truss-for-failing-to-defend-judges|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2017年4月19日，首相宣布[[2017年英國大選|提前大選]]後，《每日郵報》發表題為「擊潰破壞王」的文章，矛頭指向「非民選」的[[英國上議院|上議院]]，並形容留歐支持者是「留歐呻吟者」<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/apr/19/crush-the-saboteurs-how-hard-brexit-rhetoric-turned-leninist|title=Crush the saboteurs! How hard-Brexit rhetoric turned Leninist|first=Steven|last=Poole|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2017-04-19|accessdate=2017-04-27|archive-date=2020-12-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201209071625/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/apr/19/crush-the-saboteurs-how-hard-brexit-rhetoric-turned-leninist|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

